{"word":"ἔρημος","slug":"ἔρημος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἔρημος, ον</el></b> [the Attic form, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ assoc.\">assoc.</a> with <el>ἀραιός</el> ‘thin, sparse’]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> as <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ adj.\">adj.</a> <b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp> unpopulated, lonely <a href='B:470 14:13'>Mt 14:13</a>, <a href='B:470 14:15'>15</a>; <a href='B:480 1:35'>Mk 1:35</a>, <a href='B:480 1:45'>45</a>; <a href='B:490 9:12'>Lk 9:12</a></b> (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> focus on privacy); <b><a href='B:510 1:20'>Ac 1:20</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp> deserted <a href='B:510 8:26'>Ac 8:26</a></b> (here of a road at high noon when the heat would be intense)<b>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>c.</pp> desolate,</b> in a state of loneliness <b><a href='B:550 4:27'>Gal 4:27</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> as noun <el>ἡ <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἔρημος\">ἔρημος</a></el> <b>unpopulated region, desert, lonely place <a href='B:470 3:1'>Mt 3:1</a>; <a href='B:480 1:12'>Mk 1:12</a>; <a href='B:490 1:80'>Lk 1:80</a></b> (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pl.\">pl.</a> lonely places); <b><a href='B:490 7:24'>7:24</a>; <a href='B:490 15:4'>15:4</a> ; <a href='B:500 6:31'>J 6:31</a>; <a href='B:510 7:38'>Ac 7:38</a>; <a href='B:530 10:5'>1 Cor 10:5</a>; <a href='B:730 12:6'>Rv 12:6</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἐρημία\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἐρημόω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}